  "text": "Both prometheus/prometheus and grafana/grafana implement OpenTelemetry span creation and annotation with distinct patterns.\n\n**GRAFANA TRACING IMPLEMENTATION** (pkg/infra/tracing/):\nGrafana's tracing infrastructure is organized in pkg/infra/tracing/ with modular configuration and conditional span creation. The tracer initialization is handled through TracingConfig factory functions (NewJaegerTracingConfig, NewOTLPTracingConfig, ParseTracingConfig) in tracing_config.go that support Jaeger exporters (agent and collector endpoints), OTLP exporters (both gRPC and HTTP), and noop exporter for disabled tracing. Span creation uses the Start(ctx, name, attributes) function in tracing.go which only creates spans if the incoming context already includes a span, demonstrating conditional trace propagation. Span attribute setting uses the OpenTelemetry attribute package (attribute.String(), attribute.Int()) along with semantic conventions (semconv.ServiceNameKey). Error recording is implemented via Error(span, err) and Errorf(span, format, args) functions that set span status to error with codes.Error and record exceptions with custom attributes including Grafana-specific error metadata extraction. Trace context propagation is handled by TraceIDFromContext() for extracting trace IDs and Inject() for injecting context into HTTP headers. The ServerTimingForSpan() function formats server timing headers with trace data (00-{traceID}-{spanID}-01). Profiling integration is provided by NewProfilingTracerProvider() in tracing_profiling.go which wraps the tracer provider to annotate pprof samples with span_id labels for correlating profiles with traces.\n\n**PROMETHEUS TRACING IMPLEMENTATION** (tracing/):\nPrometheus implements lower-level tracer management in the tracing/ directory with lifecycle-aware Manager in tracing.go. The tracer initialization follows a structured approach: NewManager(logger) creates a manager with Run() lifecycle methods for starting and ApplyConfig() for configuration updates. The core span creation and configuration happens in buildTracerProvider() which constructs OTLP-based tracer providers supporting three client types: gRPC (otlptracegrpc.NewClient), HTTP (otlptracehttp.NewClient), and noop for disabled tracing. gRPC client configuration includes endpoint, insecure mode, compression (GzipCompression or NoCompression), TLS credentials, custom headers, and timeout settings. HTTP client configuration similarly supports endpoint, insecure mode, compression, and headers. Sampling strategies are extensively configured supporting four sampler types: const (AlwaysOnSampler/AlwaysOffSampler), probabilistic (TraceIDRatioBased), rateLimiting (RateLimitingSampler), and remote (Jaeger remote sampling). Sampling is applied via ParentBased strategy: sdktrace.ParentBased(sdktrace.TraceIDRatioBased(ratio)). Service metadata is embedded in traces through Resource configuration with semantic conventions (semconv.ServiceNameKey, semconv.ServiceVersionKey) plus automatically added runtime information. Both projects use OpenTelemetry v1.40.0 with compatible instrumentation libraries for HTTP and gRPC."
}

